4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, individuals who are retired
6 under the Employees' Retirement System are authorized
7 to work in certain capacities and at certain levels of
8 compensation without suspension of their retirement
9 allowance.
10 This bill would authorize any individual who is
11 retired under the Employees' Retirement System or the
12 Teachers' Retirement System with a minimum of 25 years
13 of service, has the applicable Alabama Peace Officers'
14 Standards and Training certification, and was
15 classified as either a law enforcement officer or a
16 state policeman prior to retirement to perform duties
17 as a sheriff's deputy or municipal police officer
18 without suspension of his or her retirement allowance,
19 provided the compensation earned does not exceed
20 $52,000 per year.
21 This bill would also authorize any individual
22 who is retired under the Employees' Retirement System
23 or the Teachers' Retirement System with a minimum of 25
24 years of service and is licensed to practice law in
25 this state to perform duties as an assistant district
26 attorney without suspension of his or her retirement
27 allowance, provided the compensation earned does not
28 exceed $52,000 per year.
