35 Relating to retired state employees; to amend Section
36 36-27-8.2, as last amended by Act 2025-409, Code of Alabama
37 1975, to further provide for employment authorized for certain
38 retirees of the Employees' Retirement System or Teachers'
39 Retirement System.
40 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
41 Section 1. Section 36-27-8.2, as last amended by Act
42 2025-409, 2025 Regular Session, Code of Alabama 1975, is
43 amended to read as follows:
44 "§36-27-8.2
45 (a) Any individual who is retired under the Employees'
46 Retirement System may perform duties in any capacity,
47 including as an independent contractor, with any employer
48 participating in the Employees' Retirement System or the
49 Teachers' Retirement System without suspension of his or her
50 retirement allowance provided that: (i) the individual is not
51 employed in a permanent full-time capacity; and (ii) the
52 individual's compensation from the employer in calendar year
53 2016 does not exceed thirty thousand dollars ($30,000).
54 Beginning in calendar year 2017, and each calendar year
55 thereafter, the annual earning limit shall be increased by the
56 same percentage increase as the increase in the Consumer Price
Page 2

same percentage increase as the increase in the Consumer Price
57 Index for all urban consumers as published by the U.S.
58 Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics. Any increase
59 in the annual earning limit shall be rounded to the next
60 lowest multiple of one thousand dollars ($1,000) with any
61 amount in excess of the one thousand dollar ($1,000) multiple
62 considered in determining the increase for the following year.
63 Each adjustment shall be based on the increase in the index
64 for the preceding 12-month period ending on September 30 and
65 the increase shall be effective for the following calendar
66 year.
67 (b) Any individual serving as an elected official who
68 has retired from the Employees' Retirement System may serve
69 for his or her full compensation in an elected public office
70 with the state, a county, or an incorporated municipality
71 without suspension of retirement benefits;, provided, that
72 under no circumstances shall such an individual participate in
73 or accrue additional benefits under the Teachers' Retirement
74 System or the Employees' Retirement System for that service,
75 and provided that under no circumstances shall an individual
76 whose retirement is based upon service as an elected official
77 continue in or return to the office and receive both pension
78 benefits and salary. Any provision of this subsection to the
79 contrary notwithstanding, a retiree serving as a local elected
80 superintendent of education shall not receive both pension
81 benefits and salary unless his or her compensation as a local
82 elected superintendent of education does not exceed the annual
83 earning limits provided in subsection (a).
84 (c) The responsibility for compliance with this section
